(6, 'Ayaka: Live Tour', '31', '13', '91,110', 'The concert starts with the band, the choir and the orchestra entering the stage and settled on the specialized platform before Ayaka enters the stage with applause. <br> Ayaka then performed her first song, \'hajimari no toki\' from her debut album the beginning before continuing to \'if enveloped in tenderness\', the track opener of Yu-on Club ~1st grade~.<br>Ayaka greeted the audience, asking if everyone is ready to kick some butts and play some games before singing a mashup of \'everybody goes ~Dropkick in the modern age without order~\' and \'See-saw game ~brave love song~\'.<br>As the audience clapped in excitement, Ayaka proceeds to \'tsuyoku omou\', \'Robinson\' and \'Certain things\' before talking to the audience about bravery, proceeding to \'apollo\' and \'heroine\'.<br>A white curtain goes down at the front of the stage prop and Ayaka sidesteps a little. She talked about how she enjoyed making a story for old and young generations, before proceeding to explaining the story and singing \'In Between the Sky and You\', \'LA LA LA Love Song\' and \'Close Your Eyes\' as each music video (Ayaka\'s part was edited out, changed into the pre-recorded shot of orchestra playing their instruments and the conductor giving instructions) was shown.<br>The white curtain goes up and Ayaka introduced the band before singing \'wish on a star\'. afterwards, she introduced the orchestra team and singing \'because i listened to bach\'s melody at night\' on piano, accompanied by the orchestra.<br>She then talked the audience briefly before two dancers appeared, the stage darkens as the spotlight strikes on Ayaka and the two dancers as she sang \'friends\'. After she introduced the dancers, she sang \'WHY\', \'Crescent Moon\', \'movin\' on without you\', \'midsummer fruit\', and \'love love love\' alongside the dancers.<br>As the white curtain lowered down again, Ayaka explains why she condones violence and racism, and she wishes the world would be a better place. A speech from Greta Thunberg (written specially for this concert\'s segment) on world peace and climate change displayed alongside images of violence in various parts of the world displayed. After Greta finished the first part of her speech, Ayaka sang \'peace loving people\' following the second part of her speech, Ayaka\'s rendetion of \'is it going to be sunny tomorrow?\' on piano as scenes of violence, including the recent murder of George Floyd and violent demonstrations in hong kong, was displayed. As Greta Thurnberg finished her speech and the Earth displayed on the screen, audiences applaused and praised.<br>Ayaka saying her thank yous before sitting down again, this time displaying \'Sakura\' music video in entirety. Ayaka asked the audience to sing a long with her as she sang \'Sakura\' on piano.<br>The concert ends with Ayaka singing \'beautiful\' with choir and orchestra. Once ended, she bows and exits the stage, waving to the audience who raved.', 'hajimari no toki,if enveloped in tenderness,everybody goes ~dropkick in the modern age without order~ / see-saw game ~brave love song~,tsuyoku omou,robinson,certain things,apollo,heroine,in between the sky and you,la•la•la love song,close your eyes,wish on a star,because i listened to bach\'s melody at night,friends,lover,WHY,Crescent Moon,movin\' on without you,midsummer fruit,love love love,peace loving people,is it going to be sunny tomorrow?,sakura,beautiful', '13.jpg', 'https://gagadaily.com/forums/topic/319051-create-a-label-x/?do=findComment&comment=12762222');
