(1, 'Drowned (Official Music Video)', 13, 8950283, 322210, 358011312, 'drowned.jpg', '4:23', '2020-03-20', 'Following independent success, Beyoncé was signed to Focused Entertainment and has now released her debut major-label single, ‘Drowned’. Accompanied by the single is its music video.', 14259977),
(2, 'Fake Love (Official Music Video)', 2, 8325998, 1095526, 438210440, 'fake-love.jpg', '4:02', '2020-03-20', 'BTS has had debuted with FAKE LOVE, a classic K-Pop song with all the right notes, accompanied with a music video.  In the music video, the concept of disillusionment is discussed with aesthetically dark plots and scenes.', 41782421),
(3, 'Sinister (Official Music Video)', 9, 499009, 99802, 24950472, 'sinister.png', '4:02', '2020-03-21', 'Black and white video has Poppy singing and dancing in dark space camera circling around her.  Male figures covered in black join her and start the choreography. Other scene has Poppy on a pedestal posing like baphomet and male figures around worship her.', 132886),
(4, 'Bitch Weave (Official Music Video)', 8, 266799, 2032752, 127046984, 'bitch-weave.jpg', '4:02', '2020-03-23', 'The new MBW music video redefines shock art. With the hype new EDM track playing in the background, Ariana takes to surprising viewers with disturbing scenes of her holding dead animals, simulating masturbation with food, upclose shots as she bites Adam Sandler’s nose, and random footage of pouring milk.', 1484398),
(5, 'Raini on Me (Official Music Video)', 20, 765168, 104707, 40272026, 'raini-on-me.png', '4:02', '2020-03-23', '', 289052),
(6, 'I\'m Still the King (Official Music Video)', 24, 856850, 144593, 53553125, 'im-still-king.jpg', '4:02', '2020-03-24', 'The video for I\'m Still The King opens up with Michael narrating his downfall with his mental health and ultimately how he came to have to fake his death. After the narration, there is a black and white swirl until Michael screams \"Stop!\".', 328191),
(7, 'Do You Wanna Know (Official Music Video)', 13, 3701713, 151434, 168259677, 'do-you-wanna-know.jpg', '5:01', '2020-03-25', 'Beyonce has dropped the second music video from her self-titled debut album. The single, â€˜Do You Wanna Know?â€™ was released simultaneously with the video. Directed, produced, and written by BeyoncÃ© with Steven Klein, the video runs for 5:01, 34 seconds longer than the track itself. ', 4502594),
(8, 'RUN (Official Music Video)', 2, 2191902, 851711, 125251549, 'run.jpg', '3:30', '2020-03-25', 'The music video starts with Jungkook reading a story book where a green smoke starts coming out of a book where they get sucked into the book. The song starts with RM on a tea table, sipping his tea.', 1859385),
(9, 'PARADISE (Official Music Video)', 2, 2301680, 1083143, 135392923, 'paradise.jpg', '3:30', '2020-03-25', '', 2265619),
(10, 'Feel Me (Official Music Video)', 12, 9620390, 285049, 356310745, 'feel-me.jpg', '4:28', '2020-03-25', 'Rihanna has released the music video for her debut single \"Feel Me\" off her debut album \"Say You Love Me\" to be released April 10. The video was directed by Anthony Mandler. The video runs for 4:28 seconds, roughly 30 seconds longer than the song', 27970770),
(11, 'Mouth to Mouth (Official Music Video)', 8, 738804, 339680, 84919953, 'mouth-to-mouth.jpg', '3:30', '2020-03-25', 'Today the ‘My Bitch Weave’ hitmaker, Ms. Ariana Grande, dropped her new promo single ‘Mouth to Mouth’. Featuring Chief Keef and Taylor Swift, the star-studded track is likely to make waves and gain attention before releasing her upcoming first studio album.', 795361),
(12, 'It\'s All Your Fault (Official Music Video)', 16, 786016, 209604, 52401034, 'its-all-your-fault.jpg', '4:51', '2020-03-27', 'P!nk in this music video is depicted in a vulnerable place. A room with shattered vases, pictures, windows, and flipped over furniture. The video depicts P!nk in a vulnerable state, most likely after a fight and break up.', 796924),
(13, 'It\'s Really Not You (Official Music Video)', 13, 2759857, 145256, 145255648, 'its-really-not-you.jpg', '3:29', '2020-03-27', 'The video opens with a close-up of Beyoncé. The quick bass rhythm track of the sing immediately begins as Beyoncé breathes clearly visually and bites her lip, smiling as the lyrics begin. The video is colored primarily purple, while she is sporting long, luscious golden locks and various, 80s-inspired minimalistic looks and various props.', 2359366),
(14, 'Senorita (Official Music Video)', 13, 2975681, 156615, 156614783, 'senorita.jpg', '4:02', '2020-03-27', 'The track opens with a Flamenco-dressed man playing the guitar riff repeating throughout ‘Señorita’s melody. The man stands in the middle of a sunlit courtyard, alone. The wind blows slightly and the trees sway with the wind. Beyoncé is seen in a field as the song begins, surrounded by tall grass.', 2578124),
(15, 'Sakura (Official Music Video)', 31, 4413462, 418117, 232287461, 'sakura.jpg', '13:28', '2020-03-30', 'The 13-minute visual tells a story about a high-school student named Natsuki (portrayed by Rina Kawaei), who all of the sudden lost her best friend one day before graduation. Shocked by the news, she postponed her trip to Tokyo. As the date of her departure is approaching, she needs to let go of her grief over the loss of her best friend.', 16433819),
